<span style="font-family: palatino;">'''Level 148''' is the 149<sup>th</sup> Level of The Backrooms.

== <span style="font-family: palatino;">Description</span> ==
{{Blurimage|file=lvl148r1.jpg|caption=<span style="font-family: palatino;">An image of one of the rooms found in '''Level 148'''.</span>|align=center}}
<span style="font-family: palatino;">'''Level 148''' appears to be a claustrophobic complex of rooms, resembling a basement one would find in [[The Frontrooms]]. The rooms appear extensive; however, they possess a multitude of miscellaneous objects, resulting in a cramped and narrow environment. The walls are set in a bright white tint and sometimes in a light gray. The ceiling is painted in an identical tone to the walls in each room at all times; the floor has matching qualities. Additionally, each room is behind a door, which holds the same bleached color as the walls, and each door has a small window at the top, offering a peek inside.

<span style="font-family: palatino;">Nonetheless, one can render this description pointless, as the entire area is shrouded in a thick dark ambiance. Travelers describe this as a dense layer of black fog that is impossible to see through. Any light source that one brings into '''Level 148''' loses its purpose, as even the brightest flashlights can't break through this haze. The only viable illumination at this Level is a pair of night vision goggles, as they directly impact one's visibility instead of the entire area. This quality makes the Level a hassle to explore, as the claustrophobic nature of the Level's spaces is hidden behind the gloom.
{{Blurimage|file=lvl148door.jpg|caption=<span style="font-family: palatino;">A photo of a door found in '''Level 148'''. The image has been brightened for better viewing experience.</span>|align=center}}
<span style="font-family: palatino;">As said before, the narrow nature of '''Level 148''' is mainly caused by many unique items lying all over the Level's environment. These items vary in endless ways, yet a majority of them are giant boxes and bookshelves. These boxes vary vastly in size, with the smallest measuring a mere 10cm x 10cm x 10cm, and the biggest being a stunning 5m x 5m x 3m. They hardly ever contain any materials; however, in rare cases, they can hold [[Object 1|Almond Water]] bottles inside them. Curiously, the bottles of [[Object 1|Almond Water]] have no label on them. A typical bottle found in '''Level 148''' appears to be made of transparent plastic with a smooth surface. The bookshelves don't hold any books inside them: they hardly ever serve any purpose, with the only thing found in their shelves being messy, crumbled papers with nothing written on them resembling that of a page from a standard book.

<span style="font-family: palatino;">The items can often stray away from cardboard containers and bookshelves. The most probable objects to take place are a network of cables and futuristic devices. These complex networks seem to go on forever when they appear, retaining a boundless number of mechanisms that keep expanding the wires and computers. These mechanisms are likely purposeless; this system doesn't power anything on a Level other than itself and doesn't emit any signal detectable by any human-made device. The existence of the arrangement of wires remains unknown.

<span style="font-family: palatino;">'''Level 148's''' rooms behave similarly to those of [[Level 0]], with most of them being subject to change at any moment. Walking back to a room you were in before can completely change its appearance and layout. No linearity is present in this Level's space; a door can seemingly lead to an area that you were already in, but when walking through it, the Level replaces its past with a fresh set of rooms. The rooms can also inexplicably end, with no way to progress, consequently forcing one to backtrack. This non-Euclidean nature of the Level makes any contact with a second traveler unfeasible.

{{Blurimage|file=lvl148window.jpg|caption=<span style="font-family: palatino;">A window found in '''Level 148''', showing a metal surface behind it.</span>|align=center}}
<span style="font-family: palatino;">Rarely, a window can be found in one of '''Level 148's''' rooms. These windows aren't hostile to a traveler, like [[Entity 2|the Windows entity]]; however, they carry incredibly intriguing qualities. Every window contains a few key similarities, although no two are the same. For one, they never show an interactive environment. They frequently exhibit a stale color, namely tan or bright pink, but in rare cases, they can peek into a metal or a wooden wall. They can be in any position in a room, even if blocked by an object or if it clips through matter. The latter rarely happens; therefore, most of the window's placements are reasonable. They always have bars in front of them, similar to those of a jail window. Curiously, the windows don't feel like a typical glass surface in touch, being a seemingly tough concrete material. An interesting quality of these windows is that they're seemingly completely see-through, with no documentation of anyone seeing their reflection when looking into one, which provides a dim light source to a room.

== <span style="font-family: palatino;">Mental Hazards</span> ==

<span style="font-family: palatino;">Due to '''Level 148's''' unethical environments and unhabitable nature, the Level is entirely devoid of any life. Researchers presume that any entities that resided in this Level have either perished or fled the Level due to its hazards. While the Level does contain some environmental risks, the mental hazards are much more frequent, as they can affect your state of mind after a prolonged stay. Wanderers who spend excessive time in this environment will likely suffer from a variety of problems.

=== <span style="font-family: palatino;"><big>30-40 Minutes</big></span> ===

<span style="font-family: palatino;">After approximately 30 minutes of staying in the Level, one will start to experience paranoid attacks. While in this state, a traveler will most likely peek at every corner in constant fear that an entity will attack them. The traveler will move extremely carefully, looking out for any slight danger they can find, and will focus less on finding their way out of the Level. The individual might also search every box they can encounter for seemingly no purpose. When one enters this state of mind, there's still a slight chance they will exit the Level. Once the wanderer leaves the Level, the effects will momentarily fade, and the explorer will forget everything they went through in the Level.

=== <span style="font-family: palatino;"><big>40-60 Minutes</big></span> ===

<span style="font-family: palatino;">Staying in '''Level 148''' for 40 minutes will lead to insanity in the individual, with the effects from earlier only getting worse. By this stage, the paranoia will completely change the wanderer's behavior and actions. A wanderer will interact with the ambient very cautiously, checking their surroundings every 3-5 seconds and walking incredibly slowly. One with the effects will constantly run away from a different person, nervously questioning who they are and what they have. If the other person tries to get close, the paranoid individual will always back away so that both individuals are barely close enough to converse. Furthermore, any attempts to speak to the mentally impaired individual will bring no results, as they do not answer any questions or statements. One might also experience heavy hallucinations when in this stage, most likely of [[Entity 8|Hounds]] and [[Entity 4|Deathmoths]], as well as other entities that bring any threat to a traveler. If one somehow exits the Level while being in this mental state, it will carry over for around 30-45 minutes until the effects fully fade. </span>

=== <span style="font-family: palatino;"><big>1 Hour+</big></span> ===

<span style="font-family: palatino;">After an hour of residing in '''Level 148''', any traveler will descend into total insanity. Any sane behavior that the person did at the earlier stages is disannulled, with intelligible speech constantly being said, weird and schizophrenic-like movements, and constant paranoia and dread. If one reaches this stage, they will lose their consciousness, only being a shell of who they once were. An individual in this stage will treat any living organism as a hazard, making it impossible to interact with them. Individuals start imagining non-existent objects, trying to hold seemingly nothing, and seldom speak of nothing. While they mostly run away from one, in rare cases, the individual may aggressively jump and attack. The attack itself has a wild nature to it: they will perform punches and kicks while screeching or bite one's arm and legs, evidently trying to bite the body parts off. The wanderer will forget all memories of their life, including family, friends, or others, as any mention of relatives or friends to the affected individual doesn't spark any reaction. If one escapes '''Level 148''' in this stage, it's unknown for how long the effects stay, as no one has ever escaped the Level past this stage, even when attempting to be rescued. It's estimated that all the effects will wear off after a few days, although this is speculative.</span>

== <span style="font-family: palatino;">Colonies And Outposts</span> ==

<span style="font-family: palatino;">Becuase of the Level's non-euclidean nature and major mental hazards, it's impossible to form any communities in '''Level 148'''.

== <span style="font-family: palatino;">Entrances And Exits ==

=== <span style="font-family: palatino;"><big>Entrances</big></span> ===

<span style="font-family: palatino;"> - if one enters and exits Levels too fast

<span style="font-family: palatino;"> - Discovering a damaged, white concrete wall in [[Level 51]] with a single kanji symbol written on it and noclipping through it will take you here.

<span style="font-family: palatino;"> - Stumbling upon a ruined shop in [[Level 437]] and entering it will teleport you here.

=== <span style="font-family: palatino;"><big>Exits</big></span> ===

<span style="font-family: palatino;"> - Breaking through an incredibly rare yellow window will send one to [[Level 857]].

<span style="font-family: palatino;"> - Wandering through a seldom yellow door may take one to [[Level 149]], but might also not. 

<span style="font-family: palatino;"> - Finding a well-lit room will possess an open door leading one to [[Level 181]].

<span style="font-family: palatino;"> - Corridors leading above ground leads to [[Level 369]].

